        "content": "<p>I'm using <code>6.14-rc3</code> linux with 1.88 rustc. Never had this issue before. I just did a fresh VM setup and can't compile my kernel module anymore because of this issue. Do you have any ideas what's that? Installing target didn't help.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>error<span class=\"o\">[</span>E0463<span class=\"o\">]</span>:<span class=\"w\"> </span>can<span class=\"err\">'</span>t<span class=\"w\"> </span>find<span class=\"w\"> </span>crate<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sb\">`</span>core<span class=\"sb\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>note:<span class=\"w\"> </span>the<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sb\">`</span>aarch64-unknown-none-softfloat<span class=\"sb\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>target<span class=\"w\"> </span>may<span class=\"w\"> </span>not<span class=\"w\"> </span>be<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">installed</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>help:<span class=\"w\"> </span>consider<span class=\"w\"> </span>downloading<span class=\"w\"> </span>the<span class=\"w\"> </span>target<span class=\"w\"> </span>with<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sb\">`</span>rustup<span class=\"w\"> </span>target<span class=\"w\"> </span>add<span class=\"w\"> </span>aarch64-unknown-none-softfloat<span class=\"sb\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>help:<span class=\"w\"> </span>consider<span class=\"w\"> </span>building<span class=\"w\"> </span>the<span class=\"w\"> </span>standard<span class=\"w\"> </span>library<span class=\"w\"> </span>from<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">source</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>with<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sb\">`</span>cargo<span class=\"w\"> </span>build<span class=\"w\"> </span>-Zbuild-std<span class=\"sb\">`</span>\n\nerror:<span class=\"w\"> </span>aborting<span class=\"w\"> </span>due<span class=\"w\"> </span>to<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>previous<span class=\"w\"> </span>error\n</code></pre></div>",
